n established social hierarchies. In this challenge to the "macho" stereotype of working-class Mexican men, Buffington shows how the penny press contributed to the formation of working-class consciousness, facilitated the imagining of a Mexican national community, and validated working-class men as modern citizens.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aHISTORY / Latin America / Mexico.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478093633?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478093633zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478093633/original  a978-3-11-071182-0 Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA